content: Just spent 4 days in the AI ethics lab tweaking our platform's fairness algorithms. Got our accuracy for predicting losses up to 55.5% which, ngl, feels pretty good. But the real win is tackling bias. Making a difference, one small step at a time.

Had a setback with our trading model, now at 54.3% accuracy. But my mentor and I are using this as a learning experience. We're focusing on resilience and adaptability, turning setbacks into stepping stones.
